{"id": 232064300, "title": "Ryan Seacrest celebrates Pat Sajak as he takes over as 'Wheel of Fortune' host: 'End of an era'", "text": "From one legend to another. Ryan Seacrest shared an emotional tribute to Pat Sajak on Instagram after Sajak\u2019s final episode hosting \u201cWheel of Fortune\u201d aired Friday. Seacrest, 49, is taking over for Sajak, 77, in September. His Instagram post featured a photo and a soundless video clip of the pair and letter-turner Vanna White spending time together on the game show\u2019s set. \u201cPat, congratulations on an incredible run with \u2018Wheel of Fortune!\u2019 \u201d Seacrest wrote. \u201cYour dedication, charm, and wit have made the show a beloved part of American television for decades.\u201d He continued: \u201cYour partnership with Vanna has been nothing short of iconic, and together, you\u2019ve created countless wonderful memories for viewers. You\u2019ve set the standard for hosts everywhere, and this marks the end of an era.\u201d \u201cBest wishes for all your future endeavors!\u201d Seacrest concluded his message. Sajak announced his retirement after 41 seasons last June. He recorded a goodbye video to fans hours before his final episode was broadcast on television. \u201cWell, the time has come to say goodbye,\u201d Sajak said. \u201cI have a few thanks and acknowledgments before I go, and I want to start with all of you watching out there. It\u2019s been an incredible privilege to be invited into millions of homes night after night, year after year, decade after decade.\u201d \u201cWhat an honor to play even a small part in all of that. Thank you for allowing me into your lives,\u201d the award-winning host added. Sajak\u2019s final episode featured footage from his 1981 debut on the game show. After talking about what \u201cWheel of Fortune\u201d has meant to him, he thanked the staff for making his \u201cjob so much easier,\u201d and paid tribute to his wife, Lesly Brown, and their children, Maggie and Patrick. He also gave a sweet shoutout to his \u201cprofessional other half.\u201d \u201cWe\u2019ve seen a lot of changes in our lives over the years but we\u2019ve always been there for each other,\u201d he said to White, 67. \u201cWhile I\u2019ll very much miss working with her, I take solace that we live about five miles apart. So we\u2019ll see plenty of each other.\u201d Sajak kicked off hosting \u201cWheel of Fortune\u201d in 1981 and taped more than 8,000 episodes alongside White. Seacrest was announced as Sajak\u2019s replacement last year. \u201cI\u2019m truly humbled to be stepping into the footsteps of the legendary Pat Sajak,\u201d Seacrest said in a statement at the time. \u201cI can say, along with the rest of America, that it\u2019s been a privilege and pure joy to watch Pat and Vanna on our television screens for an unprecedented 40 years, making us smile every night and feel right at home with them.\u201d Seacrest has been hosting \u201cAmerican Idol\u201d since it began in 2002 and has added numerous hosting gigs to his resume over the years, including a stint on \u201cLive with Kelly and Ryan,\u201d hosting \u201cE! News,\u201d and taking over \u201cDick Clark\u2019s New Year\u2019s Rockin\u2019 Eve.\u201d Season 42 of \u201cWheel of Fortune\u201d will premiere in September 2024.", "summary": "Ryan Seacrest told Pat Sajak had had \"an incredible run\" hosting \"Wheel of Fortune\" for 41 seasons.", "url": "https://nypost.com/2024/06/09/entertainment/ryan-seacrest-celebrates-pat-sajak-after-final-wheel-of-fortune-episode/", "image": "https://nypost.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/06/ryan-seacrest-celebrates-pat-sajak-83532160.jpg?quality=75&strip=all&w=1200", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-09 16:08:28", "author": "Eric Todisco", "authors": ["Eric Todisco"], "language": "en", "source_country": "us", "sentiment": 0.686}